26#include <sys/cdefs.h>
27__KERNEL_RCSID(0, "$NetBSD: nouveau_nvkm_subdev_volt_gk104.c,v 1.3 2018/08/27 07:38:57 riastradh Exp $");
28
29#include "priv.h"
30
31#include <subdev/volt.h>
32#include <subdev/gpio.h>
33#include <subdev/bios.h>
34#include <subdev/bios/volt.h>
35
36#define gk104_volt(p) container_of((p), struct gk104_volt, base)
37struct gk104_volt {
38 struct nvkm_volt base;
39 struct nvbios_volt bios;
40};
41
42static int
43gk104_volt_get(struct nvkm_volt *base)
44{
45 struct nvbios_volt *bios = &gk104_volt(base)->bios;
46 struct nvkm_device *device = base->subdev.device;
47 u32 div, duty;
48
49 div = nvkm_rd32(device, 0x20340);
50 duty = nvkm_rd32(device, 0x20344);
51
52 return bios->base + bios->pwm_range * duty / div;
53}
54
55static int
56gk104_volt_set(struct nvkm_volt *base, u32 uv)
57{
58 struct nvbios_volt *bios = &gk104_volt(base)->bios;
59 struct nvkm_device *device = base->subdev.device;
60 u32 div, duty;
61
62 /* the blob uses this crystal frequency, let's use it too. */
63 div = 27648000 / bios->pwm_freq;
64 duty = (uv - bios->base) * div / bios->pwm_range;
65
66 nvkm_wr32(device, 0x20340, div);
67 nvkm_wr32(device, 0x20344, 0x80000000 | duty);
68
69 return 0;
70}
71
72static const struct nvkm_volt_func
73gk104_volt_pwm = {
74 .volt_get = gk104_volt_get,
75 .volt_set = gk104_volt_set,
76}, gk104_volt_gpio = {
77 .vid_get = nvkm_voltgpio_get,
78 .vid_set = nvkm_voltgpio_set,
79};
80
81int
82gk104_volt_new(struct nvkm_device *device, int index, struct nvkm_volt **pvolt)
83{
84 const struct nvkm_volt_func *volt_func = &gk104_volt_gpio;
85 struct dcb_gpio_func gpio;
86 struct nvbios_volt bios;
87 struct gk104_volt *volt;
88 u8 ver, hdr, cnt, len;
89 const char *mode;
90
91 if (!nvbios_volt_parse(device->bios, &ver, &hdr, &cnt, &len, &bios))
92 return 0;
93
94 if (!nvkm_gpio_find(device->gpio, 0, DCB_GPIO_VID_PWM, 0xff, &gpio) &&
95 bios.type == NVBIOS_VOLT_PWM) {
96 volt_func = &gk104_volt_pwm;
97 }
98
99 if (!(volt = kzalloc(sizeof(*volt), GFP_KERNEL)))
100 return -ENOMEM;
101 nvkm_volt_ctor(volt_func, device, index, &volt->base);
102 *pvolt = &volt->base;
103 volt->bios = bios;
104
105 /* now that we have a subdev, we can show an error if we found through
106 * the voltage table that we were supposed to use the PWN mode but we
107 * did not find the right GPIO for it.
108 */
109 if (bios.type == NVBIOS_VOLT_PWM && volt_func != &gk104_volt_pwm) {
110 nvkm_error(&volt->base.subdev,
111 "Type mismatch between the voltage table type and "
112 "the GPIO table. Fallback to GPIO mode.\n");
113 }
114
115 if (volt_func == &gk104_volt_gpio) {
116 nvkm_voltgpio_init(&volt->base);
117 mode = "GPIO";
118 } else
119 mode = "PWM";
120
121 nvkm_debug(&volt->base.subdev, "Using %s mode\n", mode);
122
123 return 0;
124}
